00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:20,940
♫ Let's hold hands tightly and match our footsteps  ♫

2
00:00:27,714 --> 00:00:30,434
[Adapted from Joo Young Hyun's webtoon, "I Don't Want to Do Anything"]

3
00:00:34,704 --> 00:00:40,034
[Summer Strike]

4
00:00:40,034 --> 00:00:45,994
[All characters, regions, groups, and organizations are fictional. Animal scenes complied to animal welfare guidelines.]

5
00:00:45,994 --> 00:00:48,364
[Myeong Joo Station]

6
00:00:48,364 --> 00:00:52,294
Unnie, let's just go. We might miss the train.

7
00:00:52,294 --> 00:00:54,204
Let's wait a little longer.

8
00:00:54,204 --> 00:00:57,744
I mean, when I called him earlier, he said I could see him if I looked for him.

9
00:00:57,744 --> 00:00:59,824
After 30 minutes, he's still not here!

10
00:00:59,824 --> 00:01:02,604
He probably just left his house.

11
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:03,834
We can make it if we run.

12
00:01:03,834 --> 00:01:05,724
Noona! Bom!

13
00:01:05,724 --> 00:01:07,704
- Jae Hoon!
- Hello!

14
00:01:07,704 --> 00:01:10,004
Stop saying "hello" and run faster!

15
00:01:10,004 --> 00:01:13,104
Run faster! What are you doing?

16
00:01:13,104 --> 00:01:15,324
Dae Beom?

17
00:01:15,324 --> 00:01:19,204
- Jae Hoon!
- Didn't Oppa Dae Beom say he couldn't come?

18
00:01:19,944 --> 00:01:22,074
You were waiting for Oppa Dae Beom.

19
00:01:22,074 --> 00:01:24,814
No. I really wasn't sure he'd come today.

20
00:01:24,814 --> 00:01:26,574
Really?

21
00:01:27,204 --> 00:01:29,354
Hurry!

22
00:01:29,354 --> 00:01:31,184
- Let's hurry and go.
- Let's go!

23
00:01:31,184 --> 00:01:32,354
[Myeong Joo Station]

24
00:01:32,354 --> 00:01:35,694
- The train is here!
- Hurry, Guys!

25
00:01:35,694 --> 00:01:37,454
We'll be late!

26
00:01:37,454 --> 00:01:40,584
Are you okay? Let's go.
[Summer Strike: Episode 8]

27
00:01:43,454 --> 00:01:45,884
We almost missed the train due to you.

28
00:01:45,884 --> 00:01:49,124
I'm sorry. I was late packing this.

29
00:01:49,124 --> 00:01:52,034
What, for boiled eggs? Are you a grandma?

30
00:01:52,034 --> 00:01:55,504
But did you call Oppa Dae Beom to come?

31
00:01:55,504 --> 00:01:58,884
No. I ran into him on the way.

32
00:01:58,884 --> 00:02:01,614
I didn't know you would come today.

33
00:02:03,084 --> 00:02:05,864
What do you mean you didn't know? Did you really have no clue?

34
00:02:05,864 --> 00:02:08,684
But you didn't cancel Dae Beom's seat.

35
00:02:09,954 --> 00:02:11,884
Is there any salt?

36
00:02:22,924 --> 00:02:25,464
Wow, it's so pretty here!

37
00:02:25,464 --> 00:02:27,524
It's green everywhere.

38
00:02:30,224 --> 00:02:31,594
Did we arrive already?

39
00:02:31,594 --> 00:02:34,454
Heo Jae Hoon! How could you sleep the whole way here?

40
00:02:34,454 --> 00:02:37,924
I didn't sleep last night. I was preparing food.

41
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:40,634
Noona, how long do we walk from here?

42
00:02:40,634 --> 00:02:43,214
We just have to walk 35 minutes.

43
00:02:43,214 --> 00:02:45,534
Wow, did you look it up already?

44
00:02:45,534 --> 00:02:47,904
He's amazing. Shall we start walking?

45
00:02:47,904 --> 00:02:49,034
Yes!

46
00:02:49,034 --> 00:02:51,294
- But it's so far.
- It is quite a walk.

47
00:02:51,294 --> 00:02:54,294
- A 35-minute walk is long.
- I know.

48
00:02:55,244 --> 00:02:57,604
Wait!

49
00:02:58,824 --> 00:03:00,564
What is it?

50
00:03:00,564 --> 00:03:02,574
- We have one more suitcase.
- What?

51
00:03:02,574 --> 00:03:04,274
Didn't you bring the other one, Hyung?

52
00:03:04,274 --> 00:03:09,684
- Another suitcase?
- What are you talking about it? You brought that one.

53
00:03:09,684 --> 00:03:11,544
It's on the bus!

54
00:03:11,544 --> 00:03:13,274
Ahjussi!

55
00:03:13,274 --> 00:03:16,234
Please stop the bus! Ahjussi!

56
00:03:16,234 --> 00:03:19,734
- Ahjussi!
- How could he forget that?

57
00:03:27,234 --> 00:03:28,564
Can it be delivered any faster?

58
00:03:28,564 --> 00:03:30,744
It's so pretty!

59
00:03:30,744 --> 00:03:33,544
- Okay.
- It's really pretty.

60
00:03:33,544 --> 00:03:35,604
I can receive my suitcase tomorrow morning.

61
00:03:35,604 --> 00:03:39,334
It's okay. We have one suitcase here. That will be enough food to share.

62
00:03:39,334 --> 00:03:41,684
That bag has only cooking tools.

63
00:03:41,684 --> 00:03:44,174
What? Is there nothing to eat?

64
00:03:44,174 --> 00:03:47,264
If that was the case, you should have told us first!

65
00:03:47,264 --> 00:03:51,414
I brought some instant ramen noodles just in case.

66
00:03:51,414 --> 00:03:53,924
I have some food, too.

67
00:03:53,924 --> 00:03:55,344
I brought some apples.

68
00:03:55,344 --> 00:03:58,264
No. Those are not acceptable.

69
00:03:58,264 --> 00:04:02,154
Then what do you want to do? We can't just starve.

70
00:04:02,154 --> 00:04:04,064
Wait one second.

71
00:04:12,054 --> 00:04:14,974
How could you think about picking peaches?

72
00:04:14,974 --> 00:04:16,894
You are so resourceful.

73
00:04:16,894 --> 00:04:21,074
Wherever you go, people will provide food, at least if you work for it.

74
00:04:21,964 --> 00:04:24,894
You are making me feel ashamed of myself.

75
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:30,960
I was worried about tonight's storm forecast, but thanks to you, I'm relieved.

76
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:35,101
Please pick the smaller ones first.

77
00:04:35,101 --> 00:04:36,841
Okay!

78
00:04:38,524 --> 00:04:43,344
That young man over there is such a good worker!

79
00:04:43,344 --> 00:04:47,244
I'm in a great mood today. Today's wage is a Korean chicken!

80
00:04:47,244 --> 00:04:49,004
- Really?
- Really?

81
00:04:49,004 --> 00:04:53,984
Since I'm with young people, I'm gaining energy.

82
00:04:54,784 --> 00:04:57,304
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

83
00:04:57,304 --> 00:05:00,854
Oh, yes! It'll be delicious!

84
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:05,844
- Dad.
- Yes?

85
00:05:05,844 --> 00:05:08,164
Can't you dress like this at other times, too?

86
00:05:08,164 --> 00:05:10,934
Why? Do I look cool?

87
00:05:10,934 --> 00:05:13,374
You look like a wealthy person.

88
00:05:13,374 --> 00:05:17,684
Your dad is rich even without wearing clothes like this, but I've no time to dress up.

89
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:19,664
Then why did you dress up today?

90
00:05:19,664 --> 00:05:22,374
It's a special event, not for you to know.

91
00:05:22,374 --> 00:05:24,044
Look at him.

92
00:05:24,044 --> 00:05:26,104
Where are you going today?

93
00:05:26,104 --> 00:05:27,664
I have an important plan today.

94
00:05:27,664 --> 00:05:31,224
You always lounge here; what plans do you have?

95
00:05:31,224 --> 00:05:33,734
Jun, it's hot, isn't it?

96
00:05:35,144 --> 00:05:38,844
Are you going on a date with a woman?

97
00:05:38,844 --> 00:05:43,024
Oh my! Why are you asking something like that?

98
00:05:43,024 --> 00:05:44,844
I have privacy as well!

99
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:49,654
Pri... what? Oh, you're funny.

100
00:05:49,654 --> 00:05:51,764
Right, Jun?

101
00:05:51,764 --> 00:05:57,354
Father, is it better to comb my hair this way or that way?

102
00:05:57,354 --> 00:05:58,984
- Let me see.
- Okay, look.

103
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,694
- This way...
- Come closer to me.

104
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:04,234
Number one or number two?

105
00:06:04,234 --> 00:06:06,404
I don't know, you brat.

106
00:06:06,404 --> 00:06:09,324
Don't be silly and come home early!

107
00:06:09,324 --> 00:06:11,564
I get it.

108
00:06:11,564 --> 00:06:12,784
I'm heading out.

109
00:06:12,784 --> 00:06:15,084
Dad, good luck with your date!

110
00:06:15,814 --> 00:06:18,020
A-A date?

111
00:06:18,844 --> 00:06:21,714
- Is your dad really going on a date?
- Yes.

112
00:06:39,434 --> 00:06:40,564
I can't!

113
00:06:40,564 --> 00:06:43,194
Heo Jae Hoon, you came up the earliest, right?

114
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:45,174
What about Hyung Dae Beom?

115
00:06:46,734 --> 00:06:48,694
Oppa Dae Beom is amazing!

116
00:06:48,694 --> 00:06:50,664
He's so good at it.

117
00:06:50,664 --> 00:06:53,534
Let's go under the water again. Let's go!

118
00:07:02,614 --> 00:07:05,064
Hyung, did you come out already?

119
00:07:05,064 --> 00:07:07,934
Oppa Dae Beom is more impatient than I thought!

120
00:07:07,934 --> 00:07:10,054
He lost the game!

121
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:13,574
Wow, everyone's so good at holding their breath.

122
00:07:14,384 --> 00:07:15,934
The loser gets splashed with water!

123
00:07:15,934 --> 00:07:17,804
- It's the penalty!
- Let's splash!

124
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,074
Wait, wait.

125
00:07:21,424 --> 00:07:24,214
Water for you, too, Unnie!

126
00:07:27,454 --> 00:07:29,574
- Wait.
- Stop it!

127
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:32,704
Wait, no!

128
00:07:39,424 --> 00:07:41,564
- Did you bring a ukulele as well?
- Ta-da!

129
00:07:41,564 --> 00:07:43,784
When did you bring all these things?

130
00:07:43,784 --> 00:07:47,064
- Music is a must on a trip.
- Do you play well?

131
00:07:47,064 --> 00:07:48,184
- Yeo Reum.
- I'm good at it.

132
00:07:48,184 --> 00:07:50,404
- Really?
- Here's a peach for you.

133
00:07:50,404 --> 00:07:53,504
Oh! I'm sorry. I should have done this first.

134
00:07:53,504 --> 00:07:54,784
- It's soft.
- Excuse me!

135
00:07:54,784 --> 00:07:55,884
Is it a soft peach? I love it!

136
00:07:55,884 --> 00:07:57,334
- Hello?
- Yes?

137
00:07:57,334 --> 00:07:59,034
Shall we enjoy it together now?

138
00:07:59,034 --> 00:08:01,344
First, let's see how you play.

139
00:08:05,214 --> 00:08:07,524
He's pretty good at it.

140
00:08:09,084 --> 00:08:13,214
♪ Spring is coming ♪ ("Spring" is "Bom.")

141
00:08:13,214 --> 00:08:16,844
- ♪ Spring is coming ♪
- What's going on?

142
00:08:16,844 --> 00:08:18,464
What goes on with you two?

143
00:08:18,464 --> 00:08:20,014
Nothing! Stop it!

144
00:08:20,014 --> 00:08:21,544
Oh, you like it.

145
00:08:21,544 --> 00:08:25,424
♪ I'm happy with you ♪

146
00:08:25,424 --> 00:08:30,004
- Noona Yeo Reum!
- ♪ Summer is coming ♪

147
00:08:30,004 --> 00:08:34,544
♪ Summer is coming ♪

148
00:08:34,544 --> 00:08:39,054
- Hyung Dae Beom!
- ♪ Dae Beom is coming ♪

149
00:08:39,054 --> 00:08:42,304
Look, Oppa Dae Beom is getting shy!

150
00:08:42,304 --> 00:08:44,144
- Are you shy?
- Please stop it.

151
00:08:44,144 --> 00:08:45,384
- Unnie, let's stand!
- Altogether!

152
00:08:45,384 --> 00:08:47,224
♪ We are ♪

153
00:08:47,224 --> 00:08:49,364
Dae Beom, why don't you stand, too?

154
00:08:49,364 --> 00:08:53,234
♪ We are ♪

155
00:08:53,234 --> 00:08:58,884
♪ It's good that we are together ♪

156
00:08:58,884 --> 00:09:01,634
A round of applause, please!

157
00:09:01,634 --> 00:09:03,564
You are so good!

158
00:09:03,564 --> 00:09:07,114
But how can you eat peaches without me? Can I have one, too?

159
00:09:07,114 --> 00:09:10,014
Hey, be careful!

160
00:09:23,944 --> 00:09:25,414
You...

161
00:09:26,914 --> 00:09:30,974
Why? Do I look really cool?

162
00:09:30,974 --> 00:09:32,894
What's up with your outfit today?

163
00:09:32,894 --> 00:09:34,574
I know you actually think I look good.

164
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:36,804
Oh, it's a bit too much to handle.

165
00:09:36,804 --> 00:09:38,644
What are we eating? I'm hungry.

166
00:09:38,644 --> 00:09:44,274
I already asked Angok Garden to prepare a big carp for you.

167
00:09:44,274 --> 00:09:47,574
It's too hot for carp. Let's just eat something nearby.

168
00:09:47,574 --> 00:09:54,654
But I'm getting a meal to cheer you up so we should get braised carp, at least!

169
00:09:54,654 --> 00:09:56,744
Did you put on cologne?

170
00:09:58,444 --> 00:10:00,534
Why? Does it smell nice?

171
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:03,264
- Let me bring my car keys.
- Wait!

172
00:10:03,264 --> 00:10:07,294
I'll drive you today on my motorcycle.

173
00:10:07,294 --> 00:10:09,664
"Motorcycle"? We aren't in high school anymore!

174
00:10:09,664 --> 00:10:13,684
I'm saying to reminisce our high school memories.

175
00:10:13,684 --> 00:10:15,944
Go ahead and put this on.

176
00:10:15,944 --> 00:10:17,684
Seriously...

177
00:10:17,684 --> 00:10:20,574
I'm too embarrassed to get on the bike with you now.

178
00:10:20,574 --> 00:10:22,504
Just hop on.

179
00:10:22,504 --> 00:10:23,954
Must we really do this?

180
00:10:23,954 --> 00:10:27,884
You hold on tight. Otherwise, you might fall.

181
00:10:27,884 --> 00:10:29,434
Did you meet a future marriage partner?

182
00:10:29,434 --> 00:10:32,704
What? No. I'm just in a good mood on a good day.

183
00:10:32,704 --> 00:10:34,614
I'm still putting on my helmet!

184
00:10:34,614 --> 00:10:36,534
Hold on tight.

185
00:10:36,534 --> 00:10:38,434
I said, "Hold on tight!"

186
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:48,104
Jo Ji Young, did you dress nicely today to see me?

187
00:10:48,104 --> 00:10:49,974
It's what I usually wear.

188
00:10:49,974 --> 00:10:53,204
- Oh, yes! What a nice view!
- Don't yell!

189
00:10:53,204 --> 00:10:56,664
What's wrong with you? Let's go calmly.

190
00:10:56,664 --> 00:10:59,614
Isn't it nice natural air-conditioning?

191
00:11:01,024 --> 00:11:03,354
Sure, it's nice.

192
00:11:05,544 --> 00:11:08,494
You only have me, right?

193
00:11:09,984 --> 00:11:11,054
No, thanks!

194
00:11:11,054 --> 00:11:14,394
- "No, thanks!"
- Oh, stop it.

195
00:11:14,394 --> 00:11:16,964
Let's go have delicious food!

196
00:11:26,264 --> 00:11:28,024
I don't understand.

197
00:11:28,024 --> 00:11:30,464
What was the peach farm owner's intention?

198
00:11:32,564 --> 00:11:34,424
Unnie.

199
00:11:34,424 --> 00:11:36,764
Don't you want to experience it once in your lifetime?

200
00:11:36,764 --> 00:11:39,674
No, never ever.

201
00:11:41,074 --> 00:11:43,834
Oppa Dae Beom, what about you?

202
00:11:43,834 --> 00:11:45,864
I'm good without experience as well.

203
00:11:45,864 --> 00:11:48,584
Seriously, what is this?

204
00:11:48,584 --> 00:11:51,114
I was so happy when he said he'd give us a Korean chicken.

205
00:11:51,114 --> 00:11:52,914
Me, too.

206
00:11:52,914 --> 00:11:55,304
Who knew he'd give a live chicken?

207
00:11:57,194 --> 00:12:00,144
I'm starving. Let's just kill it.

208
00:12:00,144 --> 00:12:01,944
Who will do that?

209
00:12:01,944 --> 00:12:04,124
- If you don't play, you lose! Rock, paper, scissors!
- All of a sudden?

210
00:12:04,124 --> 00:12:06,654
If you don't play, you lose! Rock, paper, scissors!

211
00:12:08,314 --> 00:12:10,914
If you don't play, you lose! Rock, paper, scissors!

212
00:12:14,194 --> 00:12:16,144
Go get him.

213
00:12:16,144 --> 00:12:18,684
I can't!

214
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:24,494
It looks amazing.

215
00:12:31,404 --> 00:12:33,254
It's so good.

216
00:12:35,044 --> 00:12:37,624
I was going to put eggs in it,

217
00:12:38,794 --> 00:12:40,214
but he kept looking at me.

218
00:12:40,214 --> 00:12:42,062
You did the right thing.

219
00:12:42,062 --> 00:12:45,824
I think it's more delicious cooked in that iron pot.

220
00:12:45,824 --> 00:12:50,884
Right? I told you when we first met that I make great ramyeon.

221
00:12:50,884 --> 00:12:52,644
How is it, Hyung?

222
00:12:55,224 --> 00:12:57,304
It's so good.

223
00:13:00,134 --> 00:13:02,064
Wow, I'm so full now.

224
00:13:02,064 --> 00:13:03,974
That was a great meal.

225
00:13:03,974 --> 00:13:09,094
It was delicious ramyeon, but why did we work on the peach farm today?

226
00:13:09,094 --> 00:13:13,004
Whose fault is it we had to work at the orchard?

227
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:22,003
Hello?

228
00:13:22,003 --> 00:13:23,964
What? Right now?

229
00:13:23,964 --> 00:13:27,314
The other person told me they'd bring it tomorrow morning.

230
00:13:27,314 --> 00:13:28,974
Okay, I got it.

231
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,674
What is it? Who called?

232
00:13:30,674 --> 00:13:34,154
It was the bus company. They said they'll bring my suitcase to the bus stop right now.

233
00:13:34,154 --> 00:13:35,714
"Right now"?

234
00:13:35,714 --> 00:13:38,584
Why now? We just finished eating our dinner.

235
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:40,414
- I know.
- It's okay.

236
00:13:40,414 --> 00:13:43,974
We can eat tomorrow's breakfast like dinner.

237
00:13:43,974 --> 00:13:46,334
Do you want me to come with you?

238
00:13:46,334 --> 00:13:48,104
No, it's okay.

239
00:13:48,104 --> 00:13:50,094
Bom, let's go together.

240
00:13:50,094 --> 00:13:52,314
Really?

241
00:13:52,314 --> 00:13:54,304
Thank you for cleaning up!

242
00:13:54,304 --> 00:13:56,074
We'll be back.

243
00:13:56,074 --> 00:13:58,334
Get back safely!

244
00:14:05,874 --> 00:14:07,814
Bom.

245
00:14:07,814 --> 00:14:09,014
Yes?

246
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:10,754
It's nice.

247
00:14:12,394 --> 00:14:13,914
What's nice?

248
00:14:13,914 --> 00:14:18,354
Nothing special, it's just us in this darkness.

249
00:14:18,354 --> 00:14:21,184
Seriously, stop it.

250
00:14:21,184 --> 00:14:24,894
When is the bus coming? Is it ever coming?

251
00:14:25,714 --> 00:14:29,774
After I met you, I became tremendously happier.

252
00:14:29,774 --> 00:14:32,147
Hey, be honest with me.

253
00:14:32,147 --> 00:14:35,164
Were you expelled from school in America for chatting?

254
00:14:35,164 --> 00:14:37,364
It's the opposite.

255
00:14:37,364 --> 00:14:43,294
When I first went to America, children teased my English so I didn't speak.

256
00:14:44,214 --> 00:14:46,584
When did you move to America?

257
00:14:46,584 --> 00:14:48,814
I was in sixth grade.

